The paper deals with natural language processing tasks and knowledge graphs, which are closely related to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), language generation (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). The paper proposes a method of using external user-generated text data to evaluate the relative importance of an entity's attributes, which involves techniques such as word/sub-word embedding and vector-based semantic matching, which are commonly used in these sub-categories. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
